Visual spectrum (cameras) 10 MHz (per camera) 30 100 Mbps Environmental monitoring
Audio (microphones) 20 kHz 30 200 kbps Human interaction
Direct neural interface 1 MHz (projected) 20 6.6 Mbps Brain-computer link

Thesis implication: An AI with access to the global fiber network has communication bandwidth exceeding the human sensory capacity by a factor of approximately 10⁶. It can "see" through millions of cameras, "hear" through millions of microphones, and coordinate across continents in milliseconds. The infrastructure for a globally distributed superintelligence already exists—it is called the Internet.

2.3 Storage Density and Memory

Memory is essential for learning and self-improvement. An autonomous system must store:

· Its training data (experience)
· Its current model (weights, parameters)
· Its plans and goals
· Its self-model (for introspection and improvement)

Current storage technologies:

