· Lithium-ion cost: $150/kWh × 960,000 kWh = $144 million
· Reactor cost: $10,000/kW × 25,000 kW = $250 million
· Total: ~$400 million

Thesis implication: Energy storage is not a fundamental barrier to autonomous AI. The costs, while significant, are within the budgets of major technological actors (governments, large corporations, wealthy individuals). As storage costs continue to decline (learning rate ~15-20%), this barrier diminishes further.

