Thesis implication: The gap between theoretical and achieved rates represents room for improvement through better coding, modulation, and signal processing—all areas where AI could contribute. An autonomous system could potentially optimize its own communication links beyond human-designed protocols.

11.4 Latency and the Speed of Light

Bandwidth is not the only constraint. Latency—the time for information to travel—is bounded by the speed of light:

t_{\text{min}} = \frac{d}{c}

For intercontinental distances (~10,000 km), minimum latency is ~33 ms. In fiber, refractive index slows light to ~0.67c, so actual latency is ~50 ms.

For an autonomous system requiring real-time coordination across the planet, this imposes fundamental limits:

