Cognitive capacity: A modern GPU performs approximately 10¹³-10¹⁴ operations per second. At Φ ≈ 10¹² bits/J, this requires ~10-100 W. A data center with 100,000 such GPUs could theoretically approach 10¹⁸-10¹⁹ ops/s—exceeding all human brains combined by orders of magnitude.

