30.4 The Phase Transition in Civilization Itself

Yang et al. (2026) identified a phase transition in transformer learning: exponential improvement followed by power-law decay (\Theta(\mathsf{C}^{-1/6})). The same pattern may apply to civilization:

1. Exponential phase (1900-2025): Industrial revolution → digital revolution → AI revolution. Doubling times decreasing.
2. Transition (2025-2035): Diminishing returns on raw scaling; shift to efficiency, reasoning, post-training.
3. Power-law phase (2035-2100): Progress continues but requires exponentially greater investment for linear gains—unless new paradigms emerge.

Critical question: Is the power-law phase inevitable, or can new paradigms (quantum computing, reversible computing, bio-AI hybrids) reset the clock?

